<h3>DigitalOcean Droplet</h3>

<p>Don't have a DigitalOcean account?
    <a href="https://www.digitalocean.com/?refcode=475274cc0939">Click here to create one</a>
    (affiliate link - help support this free service)!
</p>

<p>
    Login to DigitalOcean and <a href="https://www.digitalocean.com/api_access" target="_blank">go to the API page</a>.
    You will need a Client ID and API Key.
</p>

<h3>Installation Requirements</h3>

<p>Run the following commands from your terminal (not within the VM):</p>
<p>
    <code>
        $ vagrant plugin install vagrant-digitalocean<br />
        $ vagrant box add digital_ocean https://puphpet.com/assets/box/digital_ocean.box
    </code>
</p>

<p>If you are on a Mac, you also need to run:</p>
<p>
    <code>
        $ brew install curl-ca-bundle<br />
        $ echo export SSL_CERT_FILE=/usr/local/opt/curl-ca-bundle/share/ca-bundle.crt >> ~/.bash_profile
    </code>
</p>

<h3>Running Vagrant</h3>

<p>Instead of running <code>$ vagrant up</code>, you will need to run <code>$ vagrant up --provider=digital_ocean</code></p>

